    {
        "id": "68bfa67e-aa18-4f79-bd9b-d0e021174e9d",
        "title": "Boxing system modes",
        "category": "Favorites",
        "subcategory": "Drill",
        "url": "https://youtu.be/Se2c2RcmOq4?is=1QSmN3IxOQWTUF1S",
        "description": "1)  fencing: fence, feint, step fake, head up/down, head off line; fake high, go low; fake low, go high;  2) fence to favorite combo, step out. Start jab, finish jab. Back to fencing.  Know your combos. Don\u2019t pause. 3) multi phase attacks. In/out of range favor strait shots.  Hooks when more planted. Lead hand out to fence ready to jab if they follow. 4) Top gear. In out, strait punches, up down, guard, back in. Not allowing opponent to breathe. Have to win round. Out work or stop opponent. 5) Pressure high guard. Cut ring. Single shots. Get them tense tired.  Step in don\u2019t allow space. Catch, step, head movement, single shots.  Collect data. Feel them slow down and then really let go. As he goes to punch guard up and close space.  6) Cruise control. Let opponent come to you.  Move feet circle. Become a ghost. Hit and not get hit. Walk him into punches",
        "is_video": false
    },
